Date: Sat, 11 Aug 2001 10:40:27 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, 10 Aug 2001 [edited

France: New case of BSE
-----------------------
A case of mad cow disease has been found in the province of Drome in
southeastern France, the first ever case found in that region. The milk
cow, one of an 80-cow troup, was found with symptoms of the Bovine
Spongiform Encephalopathy (BSE) and died on 25 Jul 2001. A test was done
and the newly published results proved that it involves BSE, reported
Agence France-Presse on Friday.

